WEBVTT

00:11.159 --> 00:15.160
She can go into people's bodies.

00:15.162 --> 00:17.235
Said the ghost
has scratched him.

00:17.237 --> 00:20.342
I yelled at whatever was here,
"Leave!"

00:20.344 --> 00:22.743
Something is so physically wrong
with her.

00:24.879 --> 00:27.181
The body was chopped up
and thrown into the harbor.

00:27.183 --> 00:30.052
This is un-[bleep]- bearable.

00:30.054 --> 00:32.787
So much pain!

00:33.958 --> 00:35.729
It's really bad in here.

00:35.731 --> 00:38.768
My name is Amy Allan.

00:38.770 --> 00:40.972
Something is not right.

00:40.974 --> 00:42.109
I see dead people.

00:42.111 --> 00:44.280
This person might have been
a serial killer.

00:44.282 --> 00:46.181
I speak to dead people.

00:46.183 --> 00:47.718
You get those chills.

00:47.720 --> 00:49.289
And they speak to me.

00:49.291 --> 00:51.830
He is darkness.
He is evil.

00:51.832 --> 00:54.839
But there's only one way to know
if my findings are real.

00:54.841 --> 00:56.508
I think she broke her neck.

00:56.510 --> 00:57.876
I rely on my partner.

00:57.878 --> 00:59.578
I'm Steve di Shiavi.

00:59.580 --> 01:01.681
I'm a retired New York City
Homicide detective.

01:01.683 --> 01:03.218
You telling me the truth?

01:03.220 --> 01:06.791
And I know every person,
every house has secrets.

01:06.793 --> 01:08.427
I think the devil is down here.

01:08.429 --> 01:09.929
It's my job to reveal them.

01:09.931 --> 01:11.097
Who the hell would do this?

01:11.099 --> 01:13.535
But Steve and I never speak...

01:13.537 --> 01:15.504
we never communicate
during an investigation.

01:15.506 --> 01:16.871
...until the very end.

01:16.873 --> 01:18.242
Who's he looking to kill?

01:18.244 --> 01:20.214
We uncover if it's safe
for you to stay...

01:20.216 --> 01:22.516
You need to get out of here
right now.

01:22.518 --> 01:23.618
Or time to get out.

01:23.620 --> 01:26.425
It was like endless darkness.

